1
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:42,879
The scenery in the suburbs is really good.

2
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,799
I really want to stay here forever.

3
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:57,359
When the bell rings,

4
00:01:58,680 --> 00:01:59,560
the city gate will be closed.

5
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:02,319
We snuck out today.

6
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,799
Don't tell anyone when we get back.

7
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:05,159
Especially my father.

8
00:02:19,719 --> 00:02:20,759
What are you hiding behind you?

9
00:02:36,879 --> 00:02:37,840
This is

10
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,000
a straw wolf.

11
00:02:43,319 --> 00:02:43,960
So cute.

12
00:02:44,879 --> 00:02:45,759
Who taught you to weave?

13
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,120
I don't remember.

14
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:53,159
Silly.

15
00:02:56,199 --> 00:02:57,400
Do you remember

16
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:59,719
when I picked you up in the suburbs,

17
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,919
you were covered in dust and looked like a beggar.

18
00:03:02,879 --> 00:03:04,360
You don't remember who your parents are,

19
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:06,280
nor where your hometown is.

20
00:03:11,719 --> 00:03:12,800
The direction to my hometown...

21
00:03:20,039 --> 00:03:21,439
Cang Feng seems to remember.

22
00:03:25,879 --> 00:03:26,680
It's by the sea.

23
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,560
By the sea?

24
00:03:38,039 --> 00:03:39,240
I really want to see

25
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:41,639
what the sea looks like.

26
00:03:56,479 --> 00:03:57,240
I just sobered up.

27
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:58,960
The sea breeze will give me a headache.

28
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:02,000
Seeing the sea

29
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,280
has been my wish since childhood.

30
00:04:08,199 --> 00:04:08,960
Li Feiyuan,

31
00:04:14,479 --> 00:04:15,840
you actually recognize me.

32
00:04:17,279 --> 00:04:17,920
It seems

33
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,000
you haven't forgotten what I said before.

34
00:04:21,439 --> 00:04:21,879
You...

35
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:22,959
Don't worry.

36
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,959
I just let Jiang Yue rest for a while

37
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:25,920
to sober up.

38
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,879
I won't let her lose her soul.

39
00:04:29,399 --> 00:04:31,000
You're now called Lu Zhiyu.

40
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,720
It seems you don't like the name I gave you.

41
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,959
Hide your edge and be loyal to your master.

42
00:04:38,759 --> 00:04:39,800
But it just ends up with

43
00:04:39,879 --> 00:04:41,160
being abandoned.

44
00:04:41,639 --> 00:04:42,519
I've been alive for so long,

45
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,160
without a fixed identity,

46
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,160
and my name is also arbitrary.

47
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:48,160
So who gave you

48
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,360
this name now?

49
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,279
A child.

50
00:04:55,639 --> 00:04:56,519
You have a child?

51
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:01,000
When I first came to this island,

52
00:05:02,199 --> 00:05:04,079
a child asked me my name.

53
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:05,480
I couldn't answer,

54
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,240
so she just gave me one.

55
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:11,000
That's so like you,

56
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,079
honest and naive.

57
00:05:18,279 --> 00:05:19,800
Hide your edge,

58
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:22,000
serve your master with loyalty.

59
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:26,879
[So your name was given by Li Feiyuan.]

60
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:32,480
[Their connection goes back a long way.]

61
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,639
[Am I jealous?]

62
00:05:47,879 --> 00:05:48,959
[Who are you]

63
00:05:49,279 --> 00:05:50,000
[thinking of?]

64
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:06,839
[It's dangerous out there.]

65
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:08,759
[Go home.]

66
00:06:09,279 --> 00:06:10,680
You pretended to be loyal,

67
00:06:11,439 --> 00:06:12,759
but you're impatient now.

68
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,279
Don't worry.

69
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:18,240
Jiang Yue is just unconscious.

70
00:06:18,759 --> 00:06:19,920
She's not dead.

71
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:23,839
What?

72
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,079
Don't you trust your master?

73
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:28,560
No.

74
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:59,000
Look how he treats his girlfriend.

75
00:06:59,079 --> 00:07:00,319
So envious.

76
00:07:02,639 --> 00:07:03,480
Girlfriend?

77
00:07:05,279 --> 00:07:07,120
I've heard that word somewhere.

78
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:10,839
They've got it wrong.

79
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,639
Jiang Yue wants to know

80
00:07:14,279 --> 00:07:15,959
if you've ever had a girlfriend.

81
00:07:24,959 --> 00:07:27,040
We wolves have only one lifelong partner.

82
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:29,879
I've never had a girlfriend.

83
00:07:31,079 --> 00:07:34,040
Save that for me.

84
00:07:35,759 --> 00:07:36,920
Li Feiyuan, I'm sober.

85
00:07:36,959 --> 00:07:37,959
Let me out of here!

86
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,000
Li Feiyuan!

87
00:07:41,279 --> 00:07:42,040
Don't make trouble.

88
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:52,319
Moon,

89
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,279
is this your brother?

90
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:58,759
What are you doing here?

91
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,079
Everyone is welcome here,

92
00:08:02,399 --> 00:08:03,360
except for me.

93
00:08:04,439 --> 00:08:05,079
You've got it wrong.

94
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,079
I'll be a good host.

95
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,720
If you have any trouble,

96
00:08:09,199 --> 00:08:10,279
feel free to ask me for help.

97
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:11,879
No need.

98
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,120
I'm just here to grocery shop.

99
00:08:14,399 --> 00:08:15,319
I didn't expect Mr. Xie

100
00:08:15,879 --> 00:08:17,240
to be so domestic.

101
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:19,240
The food in this fishing village

102
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:20,800
is too fishy for me.

103
00:08:21,879 --> 00:08:22,360
Moon,

104
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:24,000
I'm going to buy some ingredients.

105
00:08:24,399 --> 00:08:25,399
Come to my place tonight,

106
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,600
and I'll cook for you.

107
00:08:27,519 --> 00:08:28,759
Are you a good cook?

108
00:08:28,959 --> 00:08:30,319
I've been cooking for you for over a decade.

109
00:08:30,639 --> 00:08:32,399
I'm just barely

110
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,519
to your taste.

111
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:34,879
What do you want to eat tonight?

112
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:36,879
Chinese or Western?

113
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,679
Why don't we go shopping together?

114
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,440
Buy what you like.

115
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:47,919
This thing

116
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,559
must be Cola.

117
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:52,679
Yes.

118
00:08:59,200 --> 00:08:59,759
She wants it.

119
00:09:36,879 --> 00:09:38,000
What kind of cake is this?

120
00:10:04,799 --> 00:10:05,440
Hello, Huang.

121
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:07,120
Drive the car over here.

122
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:08,639
At the supermarket entrance.

123
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:22,440
What is this?

124
00:10:24,879 --> 00:10:25,399
Preserved fruits.

125
00:10:28,879 --> 00:10:29,360
Moon,

126
00:10:29,879 --> 00:10:31,480
when did you start eating these things?

127
00:10:32,759 --> 00:10:33,799
He asked me to eat it.

128
00:10:38,639 --> 00:10:39,240
I don't eat it.

129
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:41,559
You eat it.

130
00:10:57,399 --> 00:10:57,919
Bro,

131
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,559
he's about to make a secret deal.

132
00:10:59,679 --> 00:11:00,559
The location hasn't been confirmed yet.

133
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,320
I'm keeping an eye on him.

134
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:03,840
No need to pay.

135
00:11:05,399 --> 00:11:06,559
Are you going to tell me

136
00:11:06,759 --> 00:11:08,639
you're a shareholder in this supermarket?

137
00:11:09,799 --> 00:11:10,919
Bro, it's been a while.

138
00:11:13,039 --> 00:11:14,240
Since I provided the ingredients,

139
00:11:14,639 --> 00:11:16,000
can I come over for dinner?

140
00:11:16,919 --> 00:11:17,879
I'm afraid that's not convenient.

141
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:19,159
He's not going?

142
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,399
Then I won't go either.

143
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:23,960
Lunar,

144
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:25,720
do you have to make him come along?

145
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:27,440
How long have you known each other?

146
00:11:28,519 --> 00:11:30,000
We've known each other for a long time.

147
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,559
You just don't know.

148
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:39,519
Liangyue.

149
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,919
Do you want to eat beef grilled or stewed?

150
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:49,279
Eating beef is not illegal in modern times.

151
00:11:50,799 --> 00:11:51,919
You go play by yourself first.

152
00:11:52,159 --> 00:11:53,240
I'll call you when it's time to eat.

153
00:12:09,159 --> 00:12:09,600
Are you hungry?

154
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:10,840
Let me see.

155
00:12:11,039 --> 00:12:11,600
Good.

156
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:12,279
Do you want to learn?

157
00:12:16,039 --> 00:12:17,519
It doesn't taste the same.

158
00:12:18,519 --> 00:12:20,480
He probably hasn't seen Qin Yeren recently.

159
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:24,960
Try this.

160
00:12:35,679 --> 00:12:36,639
How about I teach you how to make this?

161
00:12:38,039 --> 00:12:38,720
This is not bad.

162
00:12:39,679 --> 00:12:40,360
Then teach me.

163
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:41,320
Okay.

164
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:43,879
Is that all?

165
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:44,399
Yes.

166
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:45,240
That's it.

167
00:12:53,039 --> 00:12:54,039
New scent.

168
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,080
It's nearby.

169
00:13:25,679 --> 00:13:26,639
A ball?

170
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,840
This is Romanee-Conti from France.

171
00:13:49,919 --> 00:13:50,519
She doesn't drink.

172
00:13:53,399 --> 00:13:53,960
I'll drink.

173
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:05,559
Come on.

174
00:14:05,919 --> 00:14:06,600
Eat more fruit.

175
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:07,840
Thank you.

176
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:15,720
Mr. Lu.

177
00:14:16,279 --> 00:14:17,320
Your taste is very unique.

178
00:14:26,679 --> 00:14:27,279
Mr. Lu.

179
00:14:28,519 --> 00:14:29,720
Please help take a look.

180
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:33,480
You go take a look.

181
00:14:43,679 --> 00:14:44,279
By the way, Moon,

182
00:14:45,039 --> 00:14:46,600
I'm planning to sign a new project.

183
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:47,879
I'll have more time

184
00:14:48,679 --> 00:14:49,519
to spend with you.

185
00:14:53,879 --> 00:14:54,399
How do you like it?

186
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:55,840
It's designed

187
00:14:55,879 --> 00:14:57,000
exactly the way you like.

188
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:58,759
There's a bedroom inside,

189
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:00,000
just like the one at home.

190
00:15:00,519 --> 00:15:01,440
What do you mean?

191
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:03,720
You can move in here.

192
00:15:04,519 --> 00:15:05,440
You have nightmares.

193
00:15:05,919 --> 00:15:06,679
You'll be scared.

194
00:15:22,399 --> 00:15:23,000
Where's your brother?

195
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,000
He's making a call.

196
00:15:28,879 --> 00:15:29,600
Aren't you eating?

197
00:15:32,399 --> 00:15:32,879
No.

198
00:15:34,519 --> 00:15:36,000
I hate wasting food.

199
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,440
When will Moon come home?

200
00:15:40,519 --> 00:15:41,679
I'll bring her back as soon as possible.

201
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:42,960
How soon?

202
00:15:43,799 --> 00:15:44,519
I don't need you.

203
00:15:47,159 --> 00:15:48,000
You brought someone.

204
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:49,159
Stay out of this.

205
00:15:49,919 --> 00:15:51,840
You can't achieve anything by being soft.

206
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:54,159
The longer she roams outside,

207
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:55,519
the more dangerous we are.

208
00:15:56,759 --> 00:15:57,200
Yes.

209
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:01,279
You're hurt.

210
00:16:01,519 --> 00:16:02,279
Go first.
